                     <interp inst="def1-2106-18440819" type="surname" value="NEVILLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2106-18440819" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM NEVILLE</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18440819-2106-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440819-2106-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440819-2106-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing 70lbs. weight of spun-yarn, value 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of the <persName id="t18440819-name-993">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-993" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>London and Blackwall Railway Com<lb></lb>pany</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-994" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-994" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-994" type="surname" value="BONE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-994" type="given" value="HARRISON"></interp>HARRISON BONE</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 12th of Aug. I was at the Stepney station of the Blackwall Railway. I saw the prisoner come there, and bring a bag in his hand—he took six balls of spun-yarn out of the place—he had no business there then—he used to be in the Company's employ.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-995" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-995" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-995" type="surname" value="DOYLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-995" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD DOYLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am one of the lads employed by the Railway Company—I saw the prisoner at the station on the 12th of Aug.—he said Mr. Brown had set him to work.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He said, "What do you do here?" I said I heard there were boys discharged, and Mr. Brown said he would give me work.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-996" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-996" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-996" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-996" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE BROWN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the roper in the Company's employ—I did not employ the prisoner on the 12th of Aug.—I had discharged him for four months—the bag was brought to me—I did not find it.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184408190157"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> A man told me I was wanted at the London Dock; when I got to Stepney I called in at the station; I went up stairs to the porter, and said, "I shall be obliged if you will tell me where Mr. Brown is;" he said he was not there. I went home, and then the boy and the policeman came to me—I had no bag.</p>
               <p>
